fields.Explanation: The name of the scenario the results are saved for.
The name of the Facility.
The name of the Product.

Simulations that were run for multiple replications will have outputs summarized into several statistics. The type of statistic being reported will be populated in this field. For a single replication simulation, the only Stat Type will be Mean.

The quoted time to fill as entered in the Inventory Policies table for the listed Facility / Product combination. This is the length of time from the point that an order enters the fulfillment queue at the Facility until it must be filled to be considered filled on time.
The unit of measure that time outputs are expressed in terms of.
The number of lines received by the listed Facility / Product combination.

The number of lines received by the listed Facility / Product combination where the Facility was listed as the primary source for the order as specified in either the Customer Fulfillment Policies or Replenishment Policies table.

The number of lines received by the listed Facility / Product combination where the Facility was not listed as the primary source for the order as specified in either the Customer Fulfillment Policies or Replenishment Policies table.
The number of lines received by the listed Facility / Product combination where multiple Facilities were used to satisfy the line item for the listed Product.

The number of lines rejected by the listed Facility / Product combination where the Facility was supposed to serve as the primary source as specified in either the Customer Fulfillment or Replenishment Policies table.

The number of lines received by the listed Facility / Product combination that were undelivered. This would include lines that were cancelled as well as lines that were in-transit at the time the simulation ended.
The number of lines received by the listed Facility / Product combination that were placed into backorder.
The number of lines received by the listed Facility / Product combination that were cancelled.
The number of lines received by the listed Facility / Product combination that were filled within the listed Quoted Time To Fill.
The rate of lines fulfilled on time by the listed Facility / Product combination. This is calculated as the Received Lines Filled On Time divided by Received Lines.
